U.S. Navy sailors fly a P-8A Poseidon, and Marine members from Thailand, South Korea and U.S. participate in an amphibious beach landing demonstration during exercise Cobra Gold 2017 off the coast of Thailand, Feb. 17, 2017. Cobra Gold is the largest theater security cooperation exercise in the Indo-Asia-Pacific region and is an integral part of the U.S. commitment to strengthen engagement in the region.

U.S. Coast Guard's specialized forces Maritime Security Response Team (MSRT) members conduct counterterrorism training exercise off the coast of San Diego.

The MSRT is the only unit within the U.S. Coast Guard that has counter-terrorism capabilities to conduct action against hostile targets.
The MSRT is trained to be the first responder to potential terrorist threats, deny preemptive terrorist actions, execute security actions against armed hostiles and/or non-compliant threats, and educate other forces on Coast Guard counterterrorism procedures.

The M777 howitzer is a towed 155 mm artillery piece, successor to the M198 howitzer in the United States Marine Corps and United States Army.

The lighter weight and smaller size allows the M777 to be transported by the CH-53E Super Stallion, MV-22 Osprey, CH-47 Chinook helicopter or trucks with ease to provide increased mobility and more compact storage over the M198.

SUBIC BAY, Republic of the Philippines (Oct. 05, 2018) Marines, attached to the 31st Marine Expeditionary Unit (MEU), and soldiers from the Japan Ground Self-Defense Force (JGSDF) Amphibious Rapid Deployment Brigade (ARDB) conduct AAV-P7/A1 assault amphibious vehicle operations as part of a training exercise for KAMANDAG 2 with the amphibious dock landing ship USS Ashland (LSD 48). KAMANDAG 2 is a military training exercise led by Philippines between the Armed Forces of the Philippines and U.S. military, along with participants from the Japan Self-Defense Force featuring military-to-military exchanges through various training events, capabilities development training, and humanitarian and civic assistance projects.

2018年10月5日、フィリピン・スービック湾：米比合同演習カマンダグ18(KAMANDAG 2)に参加した陸上自衛隊･水陸機動団とアメリカ海兵隊･第31海兵遠征部隊によるアメリカ海軍のドック型揚陸艦アシュランド(LSD-48)でのAAV-P7/A1水陸両用車の操作訓練。

U.S. Navy and Japan Maritime Self-Defense Force soldiers speaks with US Ambassador to Japan Caroline Kennedy during a Humanitarian Assistance Disaster Relief (HA/DR) drill during Rim of the Pacific 2016.

Twenty-six nations, more than 40 ships and submarines, more than 200 aircraft and 25,000 personnel are participating in RIMPAC from June 30 to Aug. 4, in and around the Hawaiian Islands and Southern California. The world's largest international maritime exercise, RIMPAC provides a unique training opportunity that helps participants foster and sustain the cooperative relationships that are critical to ensuring the safety of sea lanes and security on the world's oceans. RIMPAC 2016 is the 25th exercise in the series that began in 1971.

環太平洋合同演習リムパック2016期間中に行われている「人道支援・災害救援」訓練施設をキャロライン・ケネディ駐日アメリカ大使が訪問、海上自衛隊第3護衛隊群司令・真鍋浩司海将補が案内を行った。後半映像の米軍による災害救援訓練の負傷者役は自衛隊員。

リムパック2016(RIMPAC・環太平洋合同演習)は2016年6月30日から8月4日まで、26ヶ国、40以上の艦船・潜水艦、200以上の航空機、25,000人の人員が参加し、アメリカ・ハワイ沖及び南カリフォルニア沖で行われる、アメリカ海軍主催の世界最大の国際海上軍事演習。

U.S. Air Force B-52 Stratofortress from Andersen Air Force Base, Guam, conducted a low-level flight in the vicinity of Osan Air Base, South Korea, in response to recent provocative action by North Korea, Jan. 10, 2016. The B-52 was joined by a ROKAF F-15 Slam Eagle and a U.S. Air Force F-16 Fighting Falcon.
